div.p: My name is Jeremy, most know me as versx. I will have started my journey as a developer 10 years ago this August 2020 starting with Visual Basic .NET. Within the first 6-7 months of writing VB.NET I started to look into other languages such as PHP and VB.NET's counter part, C#. After a while I really started to enjoy C# a lot more than VB.NET so I decided to hang it up for VB.NET, from there it all began.

Since then I've explored so many different avenues, including game development using XNA Game Studio 4.0, Unity3D, .NET Portable Executable reverse engineering, application development with Xamarin, Xamarin.Forms, and Apache Cordova, small little PHP backends and sites to interface with my C# applications, to making cross platform applications with .NET Core. Recently I've had the pleasure of working on an educational project in Swift for macOS machines and iOS devices called RealDeviceMap that thousands of people were able to use and continue to use every day.
